OL,3,CDeath, drought and devastation: Europe
OL,4,Cfaces 'huge number' of climate extremes
OL,6,FAt the peak of a heatwave in July, 41%
OL,7,Fof southern Europe was affected by
OL,8,Fstrong to extreme heat stress, which
OL,9,Fworsens existing health conditions and
OL,10,Fcan raise the risk of illnesses such
OL,11,Fas heat exhaustion and heatstroke.
OL,13,FThe scientists warned that heat-
OL,14,Frelated deaths have increased by about
OL,15,F30% in the past 20 years, and Europe
OL,16,Fin 2023 experienced a record number of
OL,17,Fdays with "extreme heat stress".
