OL,3,CDeath, drought and devastation: Europe
OL,4,Cfaces 'huge number' of climate extremes
OL,6,FThere was a below average number of
OL,7,Fdays with snow, the report said, and
OL,8,Fthe lack of winter snow combined with
OL,9,Fsummer heatwaves meant the Alps saw
OL,10,F"exceptional glacier loss" in 2023.
OL,12,FOver the past two years, Alpine
OL,13,Fglaciers have lost about 10% of their
OL,14,Fremaining volume, the report found.
OL,16,FCopernicus director Carlo Buontempo
OL,17,Fsaid 2023 was a "complex and
OL,18,Fmultifaceted" year for climate hazards.
