OL,3,CDeath, drought and devastation: Europe
OL,4,Cfaces 'huge number' of climate extremes
OL,6,F"We know that all of these events are
OL,7,Fwithin a context of record
OL,8,Fconcentrations of greenhouse gases in
OL,9,Four atmosphere, which are the ultimate
OL,10,Fdriver of human-caused climate change."
OL,12,FThe report found that renewables, such
OL,13,Fas hydropower, wind and solar, which
OL,14,Fall rely on climatic conditions,
OL,15,Fgenerated a record proportion of
OL,16,FEurope's electricity, at 43%.
OL,18,FIt found the storms and rain boosted
OL,19,Fthe potential for wind and river flow
OL,20,Fhydropower, while there was a mixed
OL,21,Fpicture for solar.
